node.text: Few clips from My trip to the Mentawais island 🌴 🎥 by Scott Hammonds.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alessa Holloway on September 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, ocean and nature.

node.text: There was a time where I was on the WSL word tour, religiously flying and competing from country to country. Not going to lie I miss it. For the upcoming 2021 challenger series I had received a wildcard for the first four events. They went based on my 2019 ranking and I fell short due to an knee injury that year. As I am grateful for the opportunity, I’ve decided I will not compete for the 2022 champion tour. Covid has been such a crazy thing, never knowing when some random lock down may happen again😭. I also see this time as a blessing to be there for my family. But this Doesn’t mean I’m hanging up the jersey just yet. I’ll be back soon😉🤍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alessa Holloway on September 02, 2021 tagging @blessedmma. May be an image of 1 person, standing, nature and ocean.

node.text: The greatest gift that my dad has given me was the gift of surfing. Now I get to pass it on and teach my own family this greatest gift 🤍 thank you @brentbielmann for getting this shot!

node.text: Even on the flat days I’ll find a way to get the board wet, do a fun paddle work out and float around. Then sit on the beach and chill all day. Thank you @celsiusofficial for keeping me hydrated!✨
